<p>The S-polynomial is the analog of one step of the euclidean algorithm. It also has the flavor of a wronskian or an anticommutator.</p>

<p>The bag euclidean algorithm. Grab the two things (biggest?). Take remainder between them, add remainder into bag.</p>

<p>This is the shape of the buchberger algorithm.</p>

